race.comment: BRILLIANT BEAGLE (6) debuted with an eighth-place finish and then improved last start, narrowly missing out over 1100m at Gunbower by less than a length. He looks well-placed here and can go one better. ANGLING FOR INFO (2) ran a solid third last start at Wodonga over 1200m, beaten by just over a length. He strips fitter now and is expected to be right in the finish again, despite the wide draw. DUKE OF D'BROOK (8) was well-backed on debut and finished fifth at Wodonga over 1200m. He had a genuine excuse that day, and can make amends here. Follow your money. MCPHILLAMY (17) might surprise with a home track advantage. Include.
